data: A dark, comedic take on zombies told from the point of view of a recently reanimated corpse.
Anyone talking on a cell phone after a particular event becomes an aggressive, bloodthirsty zombie.

Billions die suddenly as a result of a vicious disease leaving a handful of survivors amongst the dead. Twenty-hour hours later, the dead begin to reanimate. With each passing day the dead become more attuned to their environment leaving the survivors trapped.
The second novel in the Autumn series begins by introducing new characters whose actions run concurrent with the action in the original novel, before uniting the two groups.
The third novel in the Autumn series revolves around a military bunker sealed off from the outside world.
A continuation of the Autumn series
A continuation of the Autumn series
The final book in the Autumn series

A coming-of-age novel concerning a teenager’s tumultuous summer as he deals with the joys and hardships of growing up, while learning about the value of freedom at the hands of a kind but cursed old man. Contains strong elements of traditional Haitian Vodou and zombies.
A young adult novel. Adults over fourteen turn to zombies, and young survivors battle against them.

A prison doctor injects a condemned serial killer with a formula designed to keep his consciousness awake while his body rots in the grave. But all drugs have unforeseen side-effects. Before he could be buried, the killer wakes up. Hungry. Infected. Contagious. This is the way the world ends. Not with a bang…but a bite.
A zombie apocalypse starts with undead rats emerging from Baltimore's sewers.
A young adult novel. Surviving youngsters battle adults who have become zombies.
First of a series of novels about superheroes protecting the survivors of a Zombocalypse in Los Angeles. Subsequent novels in the series: Ex-Patriots, Ex-Communication.
A young adult novel. Surviving youths battle "mothers" and "fathers" who have fallen ill.
News reporters blogging in a world that survives a zombie apocalypse.
Teen book. In a village generations after the zombie apocalypse a 16-year-old struggles with her town's religious rules until the village walls are breached and she is forced to flee into the woods.
Teen book. In the present day, U.S. teens are randomly rising from the dead, and the country is in turmoil over the question of zombie civil rights.
History is Dead: A Zombie Anthology
Twenty short stories by twenty different authors with zombies in alternate histories.
Medical doctor invents a serum that re-animates corpses.

In the city of Trois-Rivières, a mutant Asian monster escape from a boat and a zombie outbreak begins. The governments try to keep the story from the media while a high school teacher and his roommate try to survive to their zombie neighbour.

In Saint-Liconet, a zombie outbreak took place. Now it's your turn to try finding who was the first living dead among the eight last suspects. To help you, you can read interviews with witnesses, autopsy reports and proofs analysis reports.

In New York City, the dead walk the streets. From the other side of the planet, a small but heavily armed group of schoolgirls-turned-soldiers comes in search of desperately needed medicine, with a former UN weapons inspector as their local guide.
A prequel to Monster Island where a sentient zombie tries to cure herself.
Sentient zombies are intent on taking over the world killing the living with a nuclear weapon.
Sequel to Predators or Prey?. Monster hunter Wendy Markland fights zombies in the Pine Barrens of New Jersey.

Puppeteer John Chandagnac, who was sailing to Jamaica, has no choice but to join the buccaneers who have taken him prisoner. Blackbeard is assembling an empire of ruthless navy of pirates, living and undead, to voyage to the fabled Fountain of Youth. John, now known as Jack Shandy, must use magic, swordsmanship, and even his puppeteer skills to free himself from Blackbeard's deadly supernatural domination.
[On_the_Far_Side_of_the_Cadillac_Desert_with_Dead_Folks|On the Far Side of the Cadillac Desert With Dead Folks]
A bounty hunter chases his quarry in a land where the "dead folks" have re-animated due to a bacteria which has escaped a lab.
A radical Middle Eastern terrorist group plans to release a deadly bio-weapon on the American people.
The dark side of humanity as an epidemic virus terrorizes the earth.
[Pride_and_Prejudice_and_Zombies:_Dawn_of_the_Dreadfuls|Pride and Prejudice and Zombies: Dawn of the Dreadfuls]
Prequel to Pride and Prejudice and Zombies.
[Pride_and_Prejudice_and_Zombies|Pride and Prejudice and Zombies: Dreadfully Ever After]
Sequel to Pride and Prejudice and Zombies.
Set in 1968, after the first zombie apocalypse, the body of a teenage mother is discovered amongst the snow, clutching a dead baby. The dead child begins to grow.
A paramilitary force investigates an Umbrella cover facility.
A monster-creation lab is targeted for destruction.
Demons possess the bodies of the dead, including animals. One man attempts to reach his son.
[The_Stupidest_Angel|The Stupidest Angel: A Heartwarming Tale of Christmas Terror]
A novelization of Night of the Living Dead and a sequel called Return of the Living Dead.

Collection of 23 tales of the living dead by zombie fan favorites and up-and-coming authors. Includes classic tales of survival in a world populated by the living dead as well as an array of unique takes on the zombie genre.
[The_Walking_Dead:_Rise_of_the_Governor|The Walking Dead: Rise of the Governor]
It depicts the journey of Philip Blake in the early days of the undead apocalypse to his eventual rise as "The Governor" of Woodbury.
[The_Walking_Dead:_The_Road_to_Woodbury|The Walking Dead: The Road to Woodbury]

It follows the travails of Lilly Caul who finds herself coming in contact with the "The Governor" of Woodbury, a refuge amongst the zombie apocalypse that is not what it seems. The second of a planned trilogy.
R is a zombie who is a little different than his fellow Dead. He meets Julie Grigio, a Living girl, and ends up falling in love.
[World_War_Z|World War Z: An Oral History of the Zombie War]
An oral history told by many survivors of the start, during, and aftermath of the zombie apocalypse.
An earnest discussion of various survival techniques in a world threatened by zombies.
[Zombies:_A_Record_of_the_Year_of_Infection|Zombies: A Record of the Year of Infection]
A man writes in his bird watching journal about trying to survive in a zombie apocalypse.
A mosaic novel in which interconnected narratives create a unique vision of the End of the World brought about by a plague.

The newcomers tournament begins in two weeks. Captain Hanai suggests the team set goals for themselves. Everyone desires to go to Koushien, but the team lacks a consensus on how far they aim to go in the tournament. Only Mihashi and Tajima wrote winning the championship because the rest of the team lacked the resolve after losing their last game. Hanai asks Mihashi to explain what he wrote but Mihashi felt insecure about his reasoning, and says he didn't give it much thought. Abe sends Mihashi a text after practice is over to reply immediately so they could talk. The manager admits to Mihashi that she saw his text, and suggests visiting Abe instead. Tajima and another teammate offer to go with Mihashi. Abe's little brother greets them, excited to recognize Tajima. Abe believes his knee will just barely recover in time for the newcomers tournament. Waiting for their food to arrive, Abe's little brother drags Tajima off to have him teach him some pointers. Abe apologizes to Mihashi when they are alone for getting injured and breaking his promise to catch all his games, and for telling him in the beginning to never shake off his signs. Mihashi tells Abe about his happiness at feeling like he was relied on by Tajima in his last game when he shook off a sign for the first time, because he felt as if he was being relied on. He asks Abe to rely on him as well, and Abe agrees. Mihashi smiles, which shocks Abe, who hadn't seen Mihashi smile yet. Mihashi hands over the practice notes to Abe, who is surprised at Mihashi's goal of "Koushien Champions." Abe states he will state the same goal. After they eat, Mihashi and Tajima leave. On the way back, Mihashi gets a text from Kanou stating Mihoshi lost their game. Mihashi is fired up, and firmly states to Tajima that he wants to accomplish a national conquest at Koushien.
